artist_name: Louis The Child and Icona Pop
metrics_conclusion: Weekend - Tarro Remix has higher complexity than the average song  in terms Chord-Melody Tension and Chord-Bass Melody.
key_conclusion:
Weekend - Tarro Remix is written in the key of E Minor.  

According to the Theorytab database, it is the 2nd most popular key among Minor keys and     the 8th most popular  among all keys. Minor keys, along with major keys, are a common choice for popular music.  The three most important chords, built off the 1st, 4th and 5th scale degrees are all minor chords (E minor, A minor, and B minor).

metadata.artist: Louis The Child and Icona Pop
metadata.editComments: One of the rare cases where the phrasing is the interesting part. It doesn't make sense to time the phrasing differently as everything starts and ends where it should, but the chords themselves don't agree with the timing at all, confusing the ears. To add to the fire, there are two extra beats before the chorus starts.
